oneTBB provides a set of high-level algorithms to execute parallel loops and tasks easily. Some common algorithms include `parallel_for`, `parallel_reduce`, `parallel_invoke`, and `parallel_sort`.

- **parallel_for**: Allows parallel execution of a for loop.
- **parallel_reduce**: Used for performing a reduction operation (e.g., sum, min, max) over a range, combining results from different threads.

```cpp
#include <tbb/parallel_reduce.h>
#include <tbb/blocked_range.h>

int sum(int n) {
    return tbb::parallel_reduce(tbb::blocked_range<int>(1, n + 1), 0,
        [](const tbb::blocked_range<int>& range, int init) {
            for (int i = range.begin(); i != range.end(); ++i) {
                init += i;
            }
            return init;
        },
        std::plus<int>());
}
```

