To avoid deadlock, always lock mutexes in the same order. Implementing a lock hierarchy or using `std::lock()` (if you're using C++11 or newer) can help:

```cpp
std::lock(mutex1, mutex2);
std::lock_guard<decltype(mutex1)> lock1(mutex1, std::adopt_lock);
