   ```

2. **False Sharing**: If threads are working on adjacent memory locations, they might be invalidating each other's caches, causing performance degradation.

   **Example**:
   ```cpp
   struct Data {
       int value; // If multiple threads modify this, leads to false sharing
   };
   Data data[NUM_THREADS]; // Accessed by different threads

   parallel_for(0, NUM_THREADS, [&](int i) {
       data[i].value++; // Potential false sharing issue
   });
   ```

   To avoid this, you can pad your data:
   ```cpp
