       int value;
       char padding[64]; // Padding to avoid false sharing
   };
   PaddedData padded_data[NUM_THREADS];
   ```

3. **Load Imbalance**: If tasks take uneven amounts of time to execute, some threads will finish early and sit idle, wasting potential parallelism.

   **Example**: Consider a parallel loop that processes varying-length tasks:
   ```cpp
   parallel_for(0, N, [&](int i) {
       doVariableWork(i); // If work varies greatly, this can lead to imbalance
   });
