### Multi-Stage Producer-Consumer Example

Here's a complete C++ example showing how to set up a flow graph pipeline where inputs are produced, processed, and consumed:

```cpp
#include <oneapi/tbb/flow/graph.h>
#include <oneapi/tbb/flow/nodes.h>
#include <iostream>

int main() {
    // Create a flow graph
    oneapi::tbb::flow::graph g;

    // Create a queue_node as a producer
    oneapi::tbb::flow::queue_node<int> producer(g);

    // Create a function_node to process data
    oneapi::tbb::flow::function_node<int, float> processor(g, oneapi::tbb::flow::unlimited, [](int input) {
        // Simple processing: calculate the square of the input
        return static_cast<float>(input * input);
    });

    // Create a function_node as a consumer
    oneapi::tbb::flow::function_node<float> consumer(g, oneapi::tbb::flow::unlimited, [](float output) {
        std::cout << "Processed output: " << output << std::endl;
